{"title": "History of Astronomy", "description": "An attempt has been made in these pages to trace the evolution of intellectual thought in the progress of astronomical discovery, and, by recognising the different points of view of the different ages, to give due credit even to the ancients. No one can expect, in a history of astronomy of limited size, to find a treatise on \u201cpractical\u201d or on \u201ctheoretical astronomy,\u201d nor a complete \u201cdescriptive astronomy,\u201d and still less a book on \u201cspeculative astronomy.\u201d Something of each of these is essential, however, for tracing the progress of thought and knowledge which it is the object of this History to describe. - Summary from the Preface", "duration": 16727, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "14844", "name": "George Forbes"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/librivoxcdcoverart36/historyofastronomy_2005.jpg", "copyright_year": "1909", "genres": ["Astronomy", "Physics & Mechanics"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Ann Boulais"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface", "readers": [8425], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/history_of_astronomy_2005_librivox/historyofastronomy_00_forbes_64kb.mp3", "duration": 366}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 1: Primitive Astronomy and Astrology", "readers": [13667], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/history_of_astronomy_2005_librivox/historyofastronomy_01_forbes_64kb.mp3", "duration": 758}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 2: Ancient Chinese and Chaldaeans", "readers": [13667], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/history_of_astronomy_2005_librivox/historyofastronomy_02_forbes_64kb.mp3", "duration": 794}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter 3: Ancient Greek Astronomy", "readers": [13178], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/his